      "text": "How Much Do YouTubers Make? (Full 2025 Creator Earnings Guide)"
    },
    {
      "id": "t1",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Many creators dream of making money on YouTube, but the actual income varies widely depending on views, niche, audience location, and monetization strategies."
    },
    {
      "id": "t2",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "On average, YouTubers earn money through"
    },
    {
      "id": "t3",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "advertising revenue, brand sponsorships, affiliate marketing, and digital products"
    },
    {
      "id": "t4",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": ". The most common income source is advertising through the YouTube Partner Program."
    },
    {
      "id": "t5",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "In general, YouTube creators earn between"
    },
    {
      "id": "t6",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "$1 and $5 per 1,000 views"
    },
    {
      "id": "t7",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": ". This is called CPM (Cost Per Mille), which represents how much advertisers pay for every thousand ad impressions."
    },
    {
      "id": "t8",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "For example, a video with 1 million views could generate between"
    },
    {
      "id": "t9",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "$1,000 and $5,000"
    },
    {
      "id": "t10",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "in ad revenue depending on the niche and audience."
    },
    {
